-- Peru Stocks: Alicorp, Atacocha, Buenaventura, Volcan
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-05-04T20:59:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/peru-stocks-alicorp-atacocha-buenaventura-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the market close in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose for the first time this week,
gaining 0.4 percent to 22,138.03. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index
dropped 0.3 percent to 2,881.08.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
and silver producer, rose 3.9 percent to 3.20 soles after zinc
and lead rebounded in  London .  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc
and lead mining company, gained 3.8 percent to 55 centimos.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, advanced 2 percent to $40.40
after gold and silver climbed in  New York .  Alicorp SA (ALICORC1)  (ALICORC1 PE), Peru’s largest foodstuff maker,
rose 2.2 percent to 6.90 soles after Inteligo SAB analyst
Alessandra Bazan rated the stock a new buy.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper
producer, fell 3 percent to $32.30 after copper declined for a
third day in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
